betterquesting.desc: Using a redstone clock over the faucet of your smeltery drains, and a hopper under the casting table, will allow you to automate your ore processing.

betterquesting.name: Dirty Drawers
betterquesting.desc: It will be a little while before you get your Applied Energistics storage system.  Lets set up some storage in the mean time.

betterquesting.name: Drawer Control To Major Tom
betterquesting.desc: The drawer controller will act as a depository for all drawers connected within a 12 block radius (in all directions).  You can hook up a chest and conduit system to filter all of your items into the correct drawers, if you choose.

betterquesting.name: By Forge, I Tink He's Got It
betterquesting.desc: To make the more complex tools and weapons from Tinker's Construct you will need a tool forge.

betterquesting.name: Tanks For All The Help
betterquesting.desc: There are many ways to pump fluid into the smeltery or the smeltery fuel resevoir.  The easiest is the EnderIO Fluid Tank, as it requires no additional pipes.

betterquesting.name: Mobs Drop It Like Its Hot X
betterquesting.desc: I bet you'd love to get these rewards.

betterquesting.name: The Sword In The Stone
betterquesting.desc: This pack is balanced around your ability to dual wield.  And that doesn't always imply you should be using two swords.  Consider a sword and shield... as shields not only block damage, but some also have ridiculous Knockback and Thorns enchants.  Or consider wielding a helpful spell in your left hand, and a sword in the other.  The options are vast.

betterquesting.name: Never Bring Sand To the Beach
betterquesting.desc:
There are three important goals for your first few days/nights.  Coke Oven, Blast Fuirnace, and Base Defense.  The action comes quick and furiously... so take the time to fortify our base against explosions, fire, and/or pesky looters ASAP.  

§6These Tier 1 Turret Bases should help you get started on defending your property.  You will recieve some additional assistance a few quests down.

betterquesting.name: All The Power
betterquesting.desc:
No need to goto the nether for lava!
breed your way to the lava chicken and enjoy unlimited power

betterquesting.name: Alloy There Matey!
betterquesting.desc: Alloyed metals are very important.  You will find they are used in many recipes.

betterquesting.name: Lets Take It Up A Notch
betterquesting.desc: It's time to get serious about our farm.  From automating a tree farm for wood and charcoal... to using Mystical Agriculture to provide ores and resources.

betterquesting.name: Sag Millionaire
betterquesting.desc:
EnderIO Sag Mills provide an ease of operation not found in many mods because of their built in ability to push and pull items from their inventories.

§3Pro Tip:  Using Flint in your sag mill will increase the yield of your ores and their secondary outputs.  Using Dark Steel balls will increase the yield even greater.

betterquesting.name: Shiny blue rocks
betterquesting.desc: Swimming in water is a relaxing thing to do in your spare time, but what keeps shining in your eyes, there in the sand?

betterquesting.name: Portable Power
betterquesting.desc:
Power Cells allow you to remotely transfer energy from one place to another.  Similar to Tesseracts, but with no item or fluid capabilities.  Placing one Power Cell on your RF Storage Block and another on the machine that requires power, then linking them with the Power Cell Cards will allow the transfer of RF.  Higher level Power Cells allow for higher amounts of RF transfer and storage.  Multiple Power Cells can be fed from a single source if more than one Power Cell card is programmed for that source.

§3Pro Tip:  Power Cells and Ender Chests are great ways to run your automated farms without having conduits and pipes running all over the place.

betterquesting.name: Slice, Splice, and Bind?
betterquesting.desc: Many of the materials needed for EnderIO machines require technology that "taps" into the mind of the foes you encounter.  From the Zombie Logic Controller to the Enticing Crystals, you will often be asked to combine the biological with the technological in order to create new advanced equipment.  The Slice and Splice is a key part of this process.

betterquesting.name: Magical Fluids II
betterquesting.desc: You'll need a cow for at least one of these. You're welcome.

betterquesting.name: Rocket Fuel, Shaken, Not Stirred
betterquesting.desc: The Vat will be used to make a variety of fuels and fluids.  From Nutrient Distillation to power items like the EnderIO Inventory Panel and Killer Joe... to Rocket Fuel used in the creation of Airship Propellant.

betterquesting.name: Magical Fluids II
betterquesting.desc: You'll need a cow for at least one of these. You're welcome.

betterquesting.name: Mystical Agriculturel You Say
betterquesting.desc:
Mystical Agriculture is an extremely powerful system of resoure crops.  You can grow anything from Iron Ore to Wither Skeleton heads.

§2§3Pro Tip:  Growth Accelerators are placed underneath the plants they empower to grow.  The number of Growth Accelerators that will stack their effects under each plant is seemingly endless.  As with any large automated builds, be weary of lag that can be caused by too many machines in a small area.

betterquesting.name: Magical Fluids II
betterquesting.desc: You'll need a cow for at least one of these. You're welcome.

betterquesting.name: Magical Fluids II
betterquesting.desc: You'll need a cow for at least one of these. You're welcome.

betterquesting.name: Bright shiny floor
betterquesting.desc: Marble is a nice looking block to build with. Why don't you give it a try.? You'll need to collect some first.

betterquesting.name: Stay On Your Grind
betterquesting.desc:
The benefits of the Minefactory Grinder over other killing mechanisms, is that it automatically ignores baby animals.  Obvisouly this is helpful on a farm, since you do not want to kill an animal until it is fully grown, and will therefore drop meat and hides. This is exactly what you need to finish automating your livestock breeding and butchering setup.

§aTip:  §6The fisher reward will take care of all of your Seafood farming needs. Place directly on top of a moderately sized (~3x3x2 or bigger) water pool, supply it with power, and a place to put the catches.  Make sure to spread your fishers out by 4-5 blocks, as having too many, too close, will reduce their efficiency.

betterquesting.name: Wish Me Luck
betterquesting.desc: I was told of An Egg, the "Lucky Egg" the contents of which are varied.

betterquesting.name: Ol McDonald Grew Some Harm
betterquesting.desc:
Seeing as the mobs in this pack are more difficult than normal, it wouldn't be quite fair to send you out with a wiffle bat for a sword.  So craft me the basic Soulium Dagger, and I shall empower it for you.  

§6Tip:  Do not let the sword break, and dissappear... you will not have a shot an another empowered version until Care Package rune trade ins.

betterquesting.name: First steps to stars
betterquesting.desc: When we align stars it is possible to make incredible things. I finally found a way how to do it too.

betterquesting.name: Chick Master
betterquesting.desc:
Prove you are "The Chick Master" and the rewards will be plenty.

But then you must have more than enough resoures for any Task!

betterquesting.name: You Con-du-it!
betterquesting.desc: EnderIO conduits are some of the most flexible pipes in modded minecraft.  They are a common go to when automating processes and are compatible with the vast majority of machine based mods out there.

betterquesting.name: Star ingots?
betterquesting.desc: Stars are beautiful and wonderful things but not very practical when you want to try and hold them. Maybe we could come up with a way to make something like ingots out of them. Let's see if there is something in those temples that can help. Maybe if I fire starlight at some ore?

betterquesting.name: Star power
betterquesting.desc: Placing an altar down just to find out how powerful the stars are in that area is not a fun thing to do. If only there was a easier way to find places with strong stars.

betterquesting.name: Something Smells Fishy
betterquesting.desc: These automatic Fisher will periodically collect fish from water beneath them and place them into adjacent chests.  You may want to set up an ender chest system to automatically collect and transfer the items into your Cooking For Blockheads Storage.

betterquesting.name: Manipulating the stars
betterquesting.desc: Untill now I did not understand why I felt the need to do this star exploration. But finally I understand! These machines can not only benefit crystals but also myself. I just need to learn more about stars...

betterquesting.name: Better than Manure
betterquesting.desc:
Place worms down throughout your farm, they will wander the area and keep it moist and bonemealed.  They will die after a few days, so you will need to dig up dirt to find more, and replant them.

§6Tip: Lily Pads of fertility have a bonemeal effect on plants within a 4 yard radius.

betterquesting.desc: While mining I found a weird looking crystal that feels like a rock, but seems more… refined. I wonder if I can find more...

betterquesting.name: Crafting Crafting Seeds to craft Seeds
betterquesting.desc:
Crafting Seeds allow you to create variations of seed types.  If you want Iron, Stone, Gold, Glowstone, Creeper, or any other version of seeds, you must combine the related mod or resource drops, with crafting seeds, to create a seed of that variant.  Then when grown, the plant will drop an Essence of that particular mob or resource.

§6Tip:  If you end up with seeds of a particular version that you no longer need, or have too many of, you can place them into the Seed Reprocessor to break them down into useable essence of that seed type.

betterquesting.name: Juicy Fruit VII
betterquesting.desc: Sweet, filling, and most importantly, cheap. Stock up.

betterquesting.name: Juicy Fruit VIII
betterquesting.desc: Sweet, filling, and most importantly, cheap. Stock up.

betterquesting.name: Its An Animal House
betterquesting.desc: An easy way to stay organized while producing a larger quantity of livestock drops is to have pens set up for breeding and killing of livestock.  This will require one pen equipped with a Minefactory §aBreeder§f, to keep all animals within a 5x5 area in front of it breeding on cooldown.  It will also require a §aChronotyper§f machine which will remove baby animals from the breeding pen, and place them into the Kill pen.   Finally, a Minefactory §aGrinder§f will be in the kill pen awaiting the tranformation of the babies into their adult form, at which point they will be harvested for their succulent meat drops.

betterquesting.name: Turret Components
betterquesting.desc: Basic capacitors are capacitors that are basic. Once you start storing energy, you'll want to make vibrant capacitor banks, which need these.

betterquesting.name: Upgrade Them Bad Boys
betterquesting.desc: Turrets shoot things. If you haven't made a megatorch yet, are too lazy to light up around your base, and don't want to level your sword up, turrets will kill things for you. They just need power and ammo. Or you could build a wall. Its popular right now.

betterquesting.name: Spawner?  I barely know her!
betterquesting.desc: Dark glass is helpful when making a mob farm because it does not allow light to pass through.  So you may see the mobs on the other side, but it does not prevent them from spawning.

betterquesting.name: A Base of Operations
betterquesting.desc: Dark Steel is used for such things as armor, the enchanted (a useful block from Ender IO) and Teir 3 turret pieces. You could be old-fashioned and use an alloy smelter, but why not use the smeltery, or even breed some chickens?

betterquesting.name: We Can Do This Two Ways..
betterquesting.desc: Iron Golems are great at protecting your base. They have high health and hit like a truck.

betterquesting.name: This Aint No Veggie Farm
betterquesting.desc: Soul Vials are used to capture mobs, and rerelease them elsewhere.  They can also be combined with a Broken Spawner in an EnderIO Soul Binder to change the type of Broken Spawner.  The Broken Spawner can then be combined with an EnderIO Powered Spawner in an Anvil to create a Powered Spawner of the mob of your choice.

betterquesting.name: Juicy Fruit IX
betterquesting.desc: Sweet, filling, and most importantly, cheap. Stock up.

betterquesting.name: They Did The Monster Mash
betterquesting.desc: The Mob Grinder Utilities Mob is you one stop shop for all things Mob Farm related.  The main attraction being the Mob Grinder.  It is upgradeable with all sorts of enhancments including popular enchants like Looting, Beheading, and Sharpness.

betterquesting.name: Juicy Fruit X
betterquesting.desc: Sweet, filling, and most importantly, cheap. Stock up.

betterquesting.name: Roomba Schmoomba
betterquesting.desc:
Vaccuum chests are valuable additons to any farm, as they collect, store, and transfer any items picked up in a 6 block radius.  

§3Pro Tip:  You can do some miraculous things using a Cotton Swab on a low life mob.

betterquesting.name: Im Your #1 Fan
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: Meet Joe Hack
betterquesting.desc:
Different mob farms work best for different mobs.  Its hard to beat the rate of Ender Pearl return on a Killer Joe with The Ender Sword.

§3Pro Tip: The Ender Tether keeps Endermen in the area from teleporting away.

betterquesting.name: Wither Or Not
betterquesting.desc:
Setting up a Wither killing booth is a worthwhile goal for the end game.  The preparation can be a bit more challenging though.  The entire kill chamber is subject to blast and wither damage, so Reinforced Obsidian (or similar blocks) is highly recommended.

§3Pro Tip:  The placement of soul sand and wither skulls to spawn a Wither, can be automated using some simple redstone and the automatic Block Placers.

betterquesting.name: Experience The Tranquility
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: Zap Em Like Flies
betterquesting.desc: You can balance your security system around the amount of power and resources you want to dedicate to to it.  Speed upgrades can turn a slow, heavy hitting turret into a wrecking ball.  And Solar panels can turn an energy hog into a self sustaining entity.

betterquesting.name: New Quest
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: Gaze upon the stars
betterquesting.desc: Looking at the stars is very nice and relaxing, the only problem is that holding the telescope is not. Maybe we can build a solution to this.

betterquesting.name: What a Creep
betterquesting.desc:
Mystical Agriculture is a great way to grow resources, including mob drops.  You will need a hefty amount of Gunpowder to make things like Rocket Fuel in this pack, so lets start with Creeper seeds.

§6Tip:  Slaying mobs with the Soulium Dagger has a chance to make them drop their mob "chunk" which is used in the creation of seeds for that mob type.  You are in luck, as the Soulium Dagger provided in the above quest has a little extra punch to it.

betterquesting.name: They Even Have Armor
betterquesting.desc: Msytical Agriculture Armor is very strong, and was previously one of the go to sets for early game creative flight.  Unfortunately, the weather in this region causes the purity of the seeds to suffer slightly enough that the armor no longer has the ability for flight.  All of the other armor benefits are still applicable, and the armor is comparable to the armor plus high tier options.

betterquesting.name: Withe Or Not
betterquesting.desc: Using Enderman seeds, it is possile create a safe-room for your Wither Killingfarm

betterquesting.name: Minefactory is Your Factory
betterquesting.desc:
Minefactory allows you to automate process of all sorts.  Farming, breeding, mob farms, and even mass enchanting are just a few examples.  This will be key to achieving the care package goals.

Plastic is used in a wide variety of the Minefactoy recipes, and you may want to grab some rubber tree saplings to make sure you always have a healthy supply available.

betterquesting.name: The Butcher's Bakery
betterquesting.desc:
The Refridgerators are the main storage space of the CFB Kitchen.  They can be stacked two high, and dyed if desired.  Any food or ingredients inside of ANY of the storage units touching the Kitchen (including Refridgerators, Cabinets, Tool Racks, etc...) will be networked together, and taken into consideration when recipes are suggested.

§6Tip:  Your operation can be as large as you want.  It's not uncommon for CFB Kitchens to have a dozen Refridgerator units hidden under the maain kitchen, storing the massive quantities of food items they are using.  As long as they are touching at least one item from the main kitchen, they will all be within the network.  You can even control the importing and exporting of food in the refridgerators with Refined Storage busses.

betterquesting.name: All Animals Were Harmed In The Filming...
betterquesting.desc:
Assuming you will want to breed Pigs, Cows, Chickens, AND Sheep, you will need a total of 8 pens, placed in pairs with each other... back to back, resembling a " 8 "  made of fencing.  The diagram below demonstrates the set up.

+ = Fence

betterquesting.name: Frying Pan Into The Fire
betterquesting.desc: Many items you make will need to have some of the ingredients cooked.  The oven will automatically queue and cook the items you order.  Make sure to keep both cooked and uncooked foods in your storage to see the full list of available recipes, as some will require only one or the other.

betterquesting.name: Hells Kitchen
betterquesting.desc:
Any good farm needs a place to store their goods.  Constructing a "kitchen" will provide you with food storage, water source, cooking tools, and more at your fingertips.   Clicking on the Cooking Table of your Kitchen will provide you a list of all food items you can craft with the items currently in your inventory, including the storage blocks attached to the kitchen (Refridgerators, cabinets, and chests attached to the kitchen will be included.  Talk about convenient!

§6Tip:  Here are some decorative blocks to put together a kitchen of your choice.  Leave plenty of space!

betterquesting.desc: Pulverize Some Fluix Crystals And Combine The Result With Sand To Make Fluix Seed Crystals

betterquesting.name: Preventing Problems
betterquesting.desc:
One small problem with automating the breeding of livestock, is that it takes a lot longer for a baby to grow up, than it does for adults to have more babies.  Meaning, you will slowly have more and more babies sitting in the Growth Pen waiting to grow.  At some point this could reach really high numbers, eventually causing lag and TPS issues.  Take care to make sure your pens are always at a moderate population, and cull any over stuffed livestock.
§6   You can automate this by using a Veterinary Station to speed up the growth process of your baby animals. §fThis will of course increase your overall meat production as well.  You will want to set up an automated crafter that fills the syringes, sends them to the Vet station, and then collects the used Syringes back into the crafter.

betterquesting.name: Unending Bars
betterquesting.desc: So heavy, yet so light...? I'll pay you for it.

betterquesting.name: Here's My Counter Offer
betterquesting.desc: Counters are similar to refridgerators in that they have storage space which is connected to the food network for recipes.

betterquesting.desc: The sink is an incredible source of infinite water.  Incredible, because it is powerful enough to provide full water flow to an Extreme Reactor (as you will see later).  For now though, lets just worry about providing water for recipes that need it.

betterquesting.name: You Can Grow WHAT?
betterquesting.desc: You are about to open the doorway for a level of automation only dreamed of before.  This land is ripe for growing crops of all sorts... even Ore crops.

betterquesting.name: Inferium By Name, Inferium By Reputation
betterquesting.desc:
Inferium seeds and Inferium Essence are just the base level of component for Mystical Agriculture.  You will need literally hundreds of thousands of these if you plan on completing everything in this pack to its fullest.
§6The Inferium Seeds come in Tiers, each tier gives you a higher output of Inferium Essence.  When you get a decent stock of one tier, begin converting the seeds into the next tier up.  Your growth accelerators are limited, so you can't afford to waste them on lower tier seeds.

betterquesting.name: Compacting And Storage
betterquesting.desc: You have many options when it comes to organizing your Mystical Essence and drops.  If you have already achieved the Tier 4 Blood Altar and called down your Refined Storage system, you can set up autocrafting to ensure you always have what you need in stock.  Assuming you have not done this yet, a set up of crafters is an easy way to convery your essence into resources automatically.

betterquesting.name: RF, Never Leave Home With Out It
betterquesting.desc: The wirelss charger will automatically charge any RF based items within a 64 block radius.  No more worrying that you forgot to charge your magnet before you left home.

betterquesting.name: New Quest
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: Do You Mind If I Bind?
betterquesting.desc: You will find that the Soul Binder is a great tool for bending the life will of entities that you come across.  From harnessing the instincts of a zombie in a controller... or binding souls to a broken spawner.

betterquesting.name: Charged Certus Quartz
betterquesting.desc: Gather Some Charged Certus Quartz

betterquesting.desc:
Make Pure Certus Quartz By Putting these Seeds into some water you will have to wait quite a while for these to grow
(They wont Despawn)

betterquesting.name: Money Info
betterquesting.desc: Did you know that you can split and craft different bill denominations? Try it out once you earn some. I'll even give you some gold.

betterquesting.name: Luxury Even In The Worst Circumstances
betterquesting.desc:
The EnderIO inventory panel offers most of the accomodations of the bigger Storage System panels, at the cost of Nutrient Distillation.  And it works with Colossal Chests and Storage Drawers.  Just slap an Inventory Conduit onto the Chest Interface  or Drawer Controller, place a Remote Awareness Upgrade into it, and then place your EnderIO Inventory Panel at the other end.  VOILA!  You can now extract, insert, and even craft items at your panel.

§6Tip:  You can either pump Nutrient distillation into the back of your panel, or disconnect the panel and place it on an EnderIO tank to fill up.  Be careful not to run out of Nutrient Distillation, or you will have to open your chest manually until you fill it up again.

betterquesting.name: Bringing the Rocky Mountains To Your Door
betterquesting.desc: Just like the Igneous Extruder can create Stone, Cobblestone, and Obsidian using it's internal tanks, the Glacial Precipitator can make Snowballs, Snow, and Ice in it's internal tanks.  Another step in fully automating your processes.  This is a key function for automating the prodution of Gelid Cryotheum.

betterquesting.name: A Furnace Like No Other
betterquesting.desc:
The redstone furnace combines the flexibility of the EnderIO Smelter with the Speed of the IC2 Furnace.  It is, as usual, very easy to automate the input and output of all items.

§6Pro Tip:  Certain upgrades can change the function of a machine completely.  This Redstone Furnace reward makes the furnace ONLY process food items... but you gain additional speed and output.  Great for automating a Culinary Generator from things like Wheat/Toast.

betterquesting.name: Expansion Your Horizons
betterquesting.desc:
Thermal Expansion is about integrating processes between mods, and optimizing the performance of machinery.  The machine are all highly automatable and upgradeable.

§6Tip: Florbs are like fluid grenades.. throw them to create a source block of that liquid at the landing area.  Great for bridging over pools of lava or water.... or killing groups of huddled mobs.

betterquesting.name: Plates and More Plates
betterquesting.desc: The compactor is a fast and convenient way to automate the processing of, you guessed it, compressed items.  Most commonly, this will be plates.

betterquesting.name: Trashcan Smashcan
betterquesting.desc: The Nullifier is not unlike a trash can.  BUT!  It is a fancy, more expensive trash can that is sure to wow your friends.

betterquesting.name: Pulverier Power
betterquesting.desc: Not unlike the Sag Mill from Ender IO the pulverior breaks down ores into a fine dust power.  This process doubles the ore output and can even uncover secondary ore drops.

betterquesting.name: Such a Sap
betterquesting.desc:
You can now harvest the inner juices of trees to produce glue and rubber like substances that can be used interchangeably with other mods.  Simply place the Arboreal Extractor next to a tree, and it will slowly suck the sap from within the logs.  Not all trees have sap to suck, but count on most vanilla ones being compatible.

§6Tip:  Resin from trees can be processed into Rosin, which will substitute for Rubber in most cases... allowing you to make things like Conduit Binder, Cables, and Cable Insulation.

betterquesting.name: They Can Clone Anything Nowaday
betterquesting.desc: The Phytogenic Insolator Growth Chamber is a way to automate the growth of crops without ever tilling a piece of soil.  It can duplicate and grow seeds, saplings, and/or their drops using state of the art fertilizer and RF.

betterquesting.name: Induction To Industry
betterquesting.desc: The induction smelter is the Thermal Expansion version of the Alloy Smelter.  Able to create alloys of multiple types of materials quickly, and upgradeably.

betterquesting.name: Upgrade the Machine That Upgrades Machines
betterquesting.desc: As if the speed upgrades weren't enough, you can also speed up the processing rate of the machines surrouding these Thermal Mediators.  They are like AOE Effect Time Machines.

betterquesting.name: Filler Up!
betterquesting.desc: The Fluid Transposer is your one stop shop for infusing liquids to and from items.  Turn a snowball into a cryogenically  treated Cryotheum compound... turn sand into Nether Stone... or... just fill a bucket with water.  This machine can do it all.  Make sure to check the in-GUI recipes for a list of all of the amazing things.

betterquesting.name: Water Way To Go
betterquesting.desc: If you need to automate the collection of water, but do not have an endless source available, the Aqueous Accumulator will slowly collect water from the air and store it in its internal tank.  If you place water along the sides of the accumulator it will collect water much quicker, without draining the blocks on the side.

betterquesting.name: Fractioning, I Was Never Good At Math
betterquesting.desc: The Fractioning Still seperates the small molecules of solid material from the liquid compounds pulled from natural sources.  Crude Oil, Resin, and Tar are similar components.  This allows for the materials to be processed into different, more useful items.

betterquesting.name: With Great Power, Comes Great Responsibility
betterquesting.desc: All machines in Thermal Expansion can be upgraded to multiple tiers.  This will allow them to have an increased number of upgrades.  Upgrades are also more powerful depending on the tier of machine they are in.

betterquesting.name: Let Me Upgrade Ya
betterquesting.desc: Speed Upgrades will make your machines faster and more efficient, but they will also come at the price of increased energy usage.

betterquesting.name: The Beginning Of The End
betterquesting.desc: It's time to begin Extreme Crafting.  This will put your build to the test.  Your automation will need to be efficient, your determination will need to be steady... but in the end, you will be §aUNSTOPPABLE.

betterquesting.name: Out With The Old, In With The Nuetrons
betterquesting.desc:
Neutronium particles make up everything around us. They are nearly intangible and microscopic in their stature. You must harness this power in a time consuming but worthwhile process called Neutronium Collection.  Neutronium Collectors simply gather the microscopic Nuetronium particles from our surroundings, and once it has enough, produces a pile of neutrons.  This can of course be upcrafted into nuggets, ingots and blocks for the creation of unbelievelable items.
§6Tip:  Though they are expensive machines, it is wise to make as many Nuetronium Collectors as possible, as there is no ability to upgrade the machine's speed.

betterquesting.name: Dressed To Compress
betterquesting.desc: Begin your route to Extreme Crafting aptitude by crafting this Singularity.

betterquesting.name: The Sum Of It All
betterquesting.desc:
Singularities are the elemtnal representation of the different materials found on our world.  They are created by fusion compressing massive amounts of material samples down into the pureset form.  These singularities allow us to harness power in our tools, machines, and armors that were never possible before.
§6Tip:  The Nuetronium Compressor will accept any of the 10 base materials in BLOCK form only.  It takes 512 blocks of material in order to create one Singularity. Your progress on each singularity is represented in the GUI of the Compressor.  You may want to have multiple compressors running from an auto-import system... as once you put a certain material into the compressor, the machine can not switch materials until the singularity is complete.

betterquesting.desc:
"Does this modpack include Vein Miner?" No.  This modpack has Ore Excavation... which is the same thing as Vein Miner... Just a different mod/name.  Get used to it people!

§3Tip: Vein mining is rigorous activity and therefore causes you to become hungry much quicker than regular mining.  Be sure to bring lots of food.

betterquesting.name: Out of the Wood Works
betterquesting.desc: Though you will find many options for tools and weapons throughout your journey, few will be as customizeable as Tinker's.  Even some tinker's stats have been adjusted to provide more viability within this modpack, so you will want to do some thorough browsing to figure out what works best for you.

betterquesting.name: Making Ends Meet
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: I am Grout.
betterquesting.desc: Grout is the first step away from basic tools. Make some.

betterquesting.name: Setting Up The Perimeter
betterquesting.desc:
You can configure turrets to only kill hostile mobs by clicking through their GUI.  This is especially important when turrets are within range of your livestock and golems. 

§6Pro Tip: Keep in mind, that friendly units that happen to stroll into the line of fire when the turrets are shooting at hostile mobs will still take damage and possibly die.  So its best to place your turrets above the line of site to friendly mobs.

betterquesting.name: Collossal Chests Be the Best
betterquesting.desc:
Collosal Chests are exactly that... Huge Chests with hundreds or even thousands of slots to hold your goods.  Since you will not have access to Refined Storage until further into the pack (Summoned from a Blood Magic Meteor) you will want to rely on Collosal Chests and Storage Drawers to organize your inventory.

§6Pro Tip:  The max Collosal Chest in this pack is 8x8x8.  Also consider there  may be some inventory panels that will help you monitor the contents via the chest interface.

betterquesting.name: Interface is The Place
betterquesting.desc: If you want to automate the extraction or importing of any items of the Collosal Chests, you must hook your machines or transfer pipes up to the Interface of the chest.

betterquesting.name: What Core Could You Ask For
betterquesting.desc: Each Collosal Chest must have one "Core".  This is placed in the middle of one of the outside walls, and §6dictates the direction the chest will be facing.

betterquesting.name: Early Game Options
betterquesting.desc:
You will notice that mobs will make quick work of weaker building materials.  If they don't burn it down with Creeper Napalm, they will pick at it with tools until it breaks.  Be quick to replace weak portions of your base with more beefier options.

§6Pro Tip:  Certain Pressure Plates will only activate for certain entities.  Dark Steel Pressure plates only activate if a Player steps on them.  No unwanted mobs activating your doors is a very good thing.
